// Precompiled algebra shapes for the otinum isolation benchmarks.
//
// Every benchmark binary instantiates EVERY shape listed here; the runtime
// `--shapes M,N ...` flag then selects which of them actually run (default:
// all). This is the "precompile a range, filter at runtime" model: you build
// once and then explore any subset of these shapes per run, with no rebuild.
//
// To probe a shape outside this set, add an OTI_BENCH_SHAPE line and rebuild.
// Compile time and binary size grow with the number of shapes and, much more
// steeply, with the truncation order N (the product tables are generated per
// shape), so keep large-N additions deliberate.
//
// The alignment benchmark requires M >= 3 (its kernels seed spatial variables
// 0, 1, and 2); it compile-time-skips any shape below that, so the low-M
// entries here simply produce no alignment rows.
//
// Default range: the first-order sweep <1,1>..<20,1> plus the mixed-order
// shapes used in the published figures.

OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(1, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(2, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(3, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(4, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(5, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(6, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(7, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(8, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(9, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(10, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(11, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(12, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(13, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(14, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(15, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(16, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(17, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(18, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(19, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(20, 1)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(2, 2)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(3, 2)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(3, 3)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(4, 3)
OTI_BENCH_SHAPE(4, 4)
